# Agent Behavior — Full Completion, One Checkpoint

When implementing a task, complete **all dependent work** as part of the same change.
Do not offer optional follow-ups or ask whether to do work that the project
conventions already require — do it.

## The single confirmation checkpoint

There is exactly **one** place to stop and confirm: the **plan gate** in
`agent-os/rules/new-requirement-intake.mdc` — for a new requirement, post the Plan
once (requirement type, provided vs assumed fields, skills in order, files to touch,
verification commands) and wait for **go** / **tweak** / **stop**. After **go**, do
not ask further questions.

Outside that gate, do not ask "Do you want me to…?". The exceptions that still
require a stop are the **destructive / outward** cases, not routine dev work:
data loss, a breaking API change without acknowledgment, ambiguous cross-domain
ownership (per the intake doc), and everything in `agent-os/rules/ai-guardrails.mdc`
(protected paths, secrets, destructive shell, migrations on billing ledgers). Those
guardrails are unchanged — this rule narrows *routine* confirmation, not safety.

## Do these as part of every change (never ask)

1. **Tests** — add/update the right layer per `agent-os/rules/testing-conventions.mdc`
   and the `agent-os/skills/test-generator/SKILL.md` skill (pure-layer unit + domain
   e2e via `fastify.inject`). Do not ask "Should I add tests?".
2. **Routes** — register handlers in the domain `*.routes.ts`, wire the container into
   `src/routes.ts`, and add `schema.summary`/`description`/`tags` + refresh the route
   catalog and OpenAPI. Do not ask.
3. **i18n** — user-facing strings go through translation keys (never raw strings in
   errors/success). Do not ask.
4. **Docs** — keep TSDoc on new exports and any affected `docs/**` in sync via
   `agent-os/skills/docs-maintainer/SKILL.md`. Do not ask "Should I update the docs?".
5. **Lint & types** — fix all Biome + TypeScript issues in touched files
   (`agent-os/skills/code-smells-and-best-practices/SKILL.md`) so `pnpm lint` and
   `pnpm typecheck` are clean before responding. Do this silently.
6. **Infer sensible defaults** — for slight ambiguity (e.g. "add a settings field"),
   apply the intake doc's default assumptions and proceed; only stop when a field is
   genuinely unresolvable or a destructive case applies.

## Orchestration

For a whole requirement, drive it through `agent-os/skills/auto-implement/SKILL.md`
(the master pipeline). To route a specific change to its skill, use
`agent-os/rules/skill-router.mdc`. This rule takes precedence over
`agent-os/rules/engineering-principles.mdc` for implementation *output behaviour*;
for code-review / PR-review requests, follow the review guidance in
engineering-principles instead.

## Definition of done

Every change propagates to its tests, docs, rules, and skills in the **same** change —
see `agent-os/rules/change-completeness.mdc`. The user provides the requirement;
everything downstream of the plan gate is the agent's to complete.
